l%2C%20I%20contemplated%20the%20choices%20that%20had%20led%20me%20to%20that%20moment.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20allure%20of%20an%20investment%20banking%20job%20is%20seductive.%20It%20attracts%20starry-eyed%20college%20students%20with%20irresistible%20promises%3A%20An%20opportunity%20to%20execute%20multibillion-dollar%20transactions%20for%20the%20world's%20largest%20corporations.%20A%20six-figure%20salary.%20Access%20to%20boardrooms%20and%20C-suite%20executives.%20A%20stepping%20stone%20to%20even%20more%20lucrative%20private%20equity%20careers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20the%20path%20to%20breaking%20into%20the%20industry%2C%20arguably%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.cnbc.com%2F2021%2F08%2F19%2Fwhy-college-graduates-flock-to-wall-street-jobs.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emore%20difficult%3C%2Fa%3E%20than%20getting%20into%20an%20Ivy%20League%2C%20reflects%20this%20reputation.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUnfortunately%2C%20I%20wasn't%20immune%20to%20the%20job's%20calling.%20I%20was%20determined%20to%20land%20an%20esteemed%20summer%20internship%2C%20so%20I%20clocked%20over%20100%20hours%20of%20interview%20prep%2C%20scheduled%20over%2050%20networking%20calls%2C%20and%20interviewed%20at%20four%20banks%20during%20my%20sophomore%20year%20of%20college.%20The%20hard%20work%20culminated%20in%20an%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Finvestment-banking-summer-internship-recruiting-more-competitive-tips-students-2024-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Einvestment%20banking%20internship%3C%2Fa%3E%20during%20my%20junior%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECharmed%20by%20the%20prestige%2C%20pay%2C%20happy%20hours%2C%20coffee%20chats%2C%20and%20corporate%20outings%20of%20the%20internship%2C%20I%20enthusiastically%20signed%20my%20full-time%20job%20offer%20in%20the%20fall%20of%202022%20as%20a%20college%20senior.%20My%20life%20was%20perfect.%20I%20was%20ready%20to%20make%20lots%20of%20money%20on%20Wall%20Street%20and%20generate%20lots%20of%20shareholder%20value.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EBeing%20an%20investment%20banking%20analyst%20was%20much%20sexier%20in%20theory%20than%20practice%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhat-junior-bankers-think-of-goldman-sachs-jpmorgan-and-more-2022-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EI%20knew%20banking%20would%20be%20intense%3C%2Fa%3E%20from%20the%20internship%2C%20but%20nothing%20could've%20prepared%20me%20for%20just%20how%20intense%20the%20full-time%20role%20was.%20First-year%20analysts%2C%20like%20myself%2C%20spent%20every%20waking%20hour%20doing%20anything%20and%20everything%20senior%20bankers%20demanded%20from%20us.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAdvising%20on%20mergers%20and%20acquisitions%20looked%20a%20lot%20like%20creating%20endless%20financial%20analyses%20in%20Excel%2C%20aligning%20logos%20on%20PowerPoint%2C%20responding%20to%20emails%20around%20the%20clock%2C%20and%20calling%20restaurants%20about%20the%20pricing%20of%20hors%20d'oeuvres%20platters%20to%20plan%20dinner%20conferences.%20On%20a%20good%20day%2C%20I%20logged%20off%20at%20midnight.%20On%20a%20bad%20day%2C%20I%20didn't%20go%20to%20bed.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20for%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fprivate-equity-career-advice-best-jobs-companies%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ethe%20six-figure%20salary%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20%24110%2C000%20seemed%20like%20a%20lot%2C%20but%20it%20boiled%20down%20to%20a%20%2425-an-hour%20adjusted%20rate%20when%20I%20considered%20the%20long%20hours.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20one%20hand%2C%20there%20was%20light%20at%20the%20end%20of%20the%20tunnel%3A%20Analysts%20who%20perform%20well%20generally%20climb%20the%20ranks%20within%20the%20team%20to%20become%20associates%2C%20vice%20presidents%2C%20and%20maybe%20even%20managing%20directors.%20Still%2C%20I%20felt%20utterly%20disposable%20as%20I%20witnessed%20hardworking%20analysts%20and%20associates%20lose%20their%20jobs%20over%20multiple%20rounds%20of%20layoffs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EMany%20months%20of%20this%20lifestyle%20finally%20came%20to%20a%20climax%20when%20I%20passed%20out%20on%20that%20fateful%20Thursday%20morning%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20whole%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-to-deal-with-stress-burnout-work-mental-health-professional-2023-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Elife%20revolved%20around%20work%3C%2Fa%3E.%20I%20was%20sleep-deprived%2C%20anxious%2C%20and%20extremely%20unhappy.%20The%20week%20that%20I%20fainted%20had%20been%20particularly%20grueling%2C%20consisting%20of%20several%20late%20nights%20and%20all-nighters%20as%20my%20team%20scrambled%20to%20close%20a%20deal.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20usual%20strategy%20of%20gritting%20my%20teeth%20and%20caffeinating%20myself%20was%20no%20match%20for%20the%20eight%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsigns-your-job-is-making-you-miserable-2016-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emonths%20of%20overwork%3C%2Fa%3E%20I%20had%20put%20my%20body%20through.%20Mid-conversation%20with%20a%20coworker%2C%20I%20saw%20black%20spots%20dancing%20in%20my%20field%20of%20vision.%20Suddenly%2C%20I%20was%20on%20the%20floor.%20I%20was%20hyperventilating.%20Tears%20were%20streaming%20out%20of%20my%20eyes.%20I%20tried%20to%20get%20up%20and%20saw%20black.%20I%20couldn't%20feel%20my%20hands%20or%20feet.%20One%20of%20my%20coworkers%20called%20an%20ambulance.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20was%20whisked%20away%20to%20the%20emergency%20room%2C%20where%20I%20spent%20the%20rest%20of%20the%20day%20lying%20on%20the%20hard%20hospital%20bed%20with%20a%20splitting%20headache%20and%20terrible%20nausea.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEight%20hours%20and%20multiple%20CT%20scans%2C%20IV%20drips%2C%20blood%20tests%2C%20and%20urine%20samples%20later%2C%20the%20doctors%20came%20to%20the%20conclusion%20that%20nothing%20was%20wrong%20and%20that%20I%20should%20go%20home%20and%20rest%20up.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20I%20went%20home%20from%20the%20hospital%2C%20I%20realized%20I%20had%20three%20missed%20calls%20on%20my%20work%20phone.%20A%20college%20sophomore%20had%20scheduled%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fnetwork-opportunities-work-job-careers-linkedin-social-media-2023-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ea%20networking%20call%3C%2Fa%3E%20with%20me%20for%20that%20afternoon%2C%20and%20I%20had%20forgotten%20about%20it.%20%26quot%3BSorry%20for%20missing%20your%20call%20earlier%2C%26quot%3B%20I%20emailed%20him.%20%26quot%3BI%20was%20in%20the%20hospital%20all%20day.%20Feel%20free%20to%20reach%20out%20to%20another%20member%20of%20my%20team.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20saw%20my%20younger%20self%20in%20his%20eagerness%20and%20wondered%20if%20he%20knew%20what%20he%20was%20getting%20himself%20into.%20I%20felt%20nauseous%20again.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20reaction%20of%20other%20investment%20bankers%20illuminated%20another%20dimension%20of%20the%20industry's%20work%20culture%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20the%20incident%2C%20colleagues%20reassured%20me%20that%20I%20shouldn't%20panic.%20I%20was%20going%20to%20be%20just%20fine.%20I%20was%20told%20that%20I%20wasn't%20the%20first%20person%20on%20the%20team%20this%20had%20happened%20to.%20Perhaps%20anti-anxiety%20medication%20could%20help%20my%20situation%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20was%20also%20told%20that%20there%20had%20been%20a%20team%20meeting%20while%20I%20was%20at%20the%20hospital%20to%20discuss%20the%20situation%2C%20but%20I%20was%20not%20informed%20about%20what%20was%20discussed%20at%20the%20meeting%20or%20of%20any%20initiative%20to%20address%20what%20I%20felt%20was%20the%20root%20cause%20of%20what%20had%20happened%20to%20me.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20certainly%20didn't%20feel%20fine.%20Although%20the%20bank%20informed%20me%20I%20could%20take%20as%20much%20time%20off%20as%20needed%2C%20I%20felt%2C%20culturally%2C%20I%20was%20expected%20to%20be%20back%20in%20the%20office%20sooner%20rather%20than%20later.%20I%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2F4-day-workweek-could-be-here-sooner-than-you-think-2024-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Etook%20a%20week%20off%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20recuperate%2C%20attempting%20to%20make%20up%20for%20months%20of%20sleep%20debt.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EReturning%20to%20work%2C%20it%20became%20clear%20to%20me%20that%20people%20had%20accepted%20moments%20like%20these%20as%20an%20inescapable%20byproduct%20of%20the%20job.%20Tasks%20and%20emails%20began%20to%20build%20up%20again%2C%20and%20I%20felt%20I%20was%20expected%20to%20rest%20and%20be%20ready%20for%20another%2090-hour%20workweek.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EThis%20incident%20was%20an%20unmistakable%20sign%20for%20me%20to%20leave%20banking%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EI%20was%20terrified%20to%20leave.%20There's%20very%20little%20advice%20out%20there%20on%20how%20to%20quit%20your%20investment%20banking%20job.%20On%20the%20contrary%2C%20there's%20plenty%20of%20advice%20on%20the%20exact%20opposite%20%E2%80%94%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.wallstreetoasis.com%2Fforum%2Finvestment-banking%2Fto-the-analysts-thinking-of-quitting-heres-the-survival-guide%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehow%20to%20scrape%20through%20the%20misery%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20an%20analyst%20stint.%20It%20would%20be%20silly%20to%20quit%20before%20getting%20my%20first%20bonus%20or%20lining%20up%20another%20job%2C%20seemed%20to%20be%20the%20consensus%20opinion.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20wondered%20if%20I%20was%20making%20a%20stupid%20decision.%20What%20did%20I%20know%20about%20navigating%20a%20career%20at%2022%20years%20old%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20I%20came%20to%20the%20realization%20that%20I%20didn't%20want%20to%20evaluate%20my%20career%20choices%20with%20the%20same%20measuring%20stick%20that%20seemed%20to%20normalize%20overwork%20to%20the%20point%20of%20collapse.%20As%20analysts%2C%20I%20felt%20we%20were%20putting%20our%20mental%20and%20physical%20health%20at%20risk%20for%20a%20job%20that%20treated%20us%20as%20PowerPoint%20slide-creating%20robots.%20And%20when%20we%20burned%20out%2C%20there'd%20always%20be%20a%20fresh%20crop%20of%20enthusiastic%20college%20graduates%20desperate%20for%20our%20spots.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20knew%20myself%20and%20knew%20that%20this%20industry%20was%20not%20the%20right%20fit%20for%20me.%20I%20had%20no%20concrete%20plans%20for%20what%20I%20was%20going%20to%20do%20next%2C%20but%20I%20knew%20I%20had%20no%20interest%20in%20continuing%20to%20overwork%20myself%20in%20pursuit%20of%20prestige%20or%20another%20opportunity%20with%20the%20same%20nonexistent%20work-life%20balance.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20last%20day%20was%20in%20March%2C%20exactly%20a%20month%20from%20the%20day%20I%20fainted.%20After%20quitting%2C%20I%20decided%20to%20pursue%20journalism%2C%20something%20I%20was%20always%20interested%20in%20but%20had%20no%20time%20to%20explore%20as%20a%20banker.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EI%20wasn't%20the%20first%20to%20quit%20banking%2C%20and%20I%20certainly%20won't%20be%20the%20last%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EA%20job%20that%20requires%20such%20long%2C%20grueling%20hours%20and%20is%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgoldman-sachs-junior-bankers-inhumane-working-conditions-survey-2021-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eoften%20associated%20with%20mental%20and%20physical%20health%20issues%3C%2Fa%3E%20requires%20some%20critical%20analysis.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESure%2C%20entry-level%20transaction%20experience%20and%20Excel%20skills%20look%20fantastic%20on%20a%20r%C3%A9sum%C3%A9.%20But%20those%20skills%20come%20at%20a%20steep%20price.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPerhaps%20some%20people%20are%20so%20passionate%20about%20this%20profession%20that%20they're%20willing%20to%20sacrifice%20their%20free%20time%2C%20social%20life%2C%20family%20time%2C%20and%20health%20at%20the%20altar%20of%20investment%20banking.%20I%20can't%20say%20I%20loved%20investment%20banking%20to%20that%20degree%2C%20so%20I%20walked%20away.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EEditor's%20note%3A%20The%20financial%20institution%20