erified%20his%20employment%20history.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20started%20law%20school%20in%20the%20late%20nineties.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBy%20the%20time%20I%20graduated%20in%202003%2C%20the%20dot-com%20boom%20had%20happened%2C%20the%20dot-com%20bust%20had%20happened%2C%20Google%20had%20been%20invented%2C%20and%20the%20internet%20had%20become%20mainstream.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESeven%20years%20into%20my%20career%2C%20which%20took%20me%20from%20litigation%20to%20corporate%20law%2C%20and%20from%20India%20to%20Australia%2C%20I%20began%20taking%20an%20interest%20in%20tech.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20realized%20I%20was%20sitting%20far%20away%20from%20the%20sidelines%20of%20the%20tech%20industry%20and%20had%20no%20way%20to%20get%20in.%20I%20was%20doing%20well%20in%20my%20legal%20career%2C%20but%20it%20didn't%20align%20with%20who%20I%20was%20as%20a%20person%3A%20I%20was%20more%20interested%20in%20creating%20things%20than%20calculating%20risks%20and%20reviewing%20contracts.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOver%20the%20next%20few%20years%2C%20I%20tried%20various%20things%3A%20I%20worked%20on%20two%20startup%20attempts%20while%20in%20my%20full-time%20job%2C%20then%20switched%20to%20a%20business%20role%20within%20the%20company.%20I%20quit%20my%20job%20cold%20turkey%20to%20build%20a%20tech%20startup%2C%20which%20cost%20me%20six%20figures%20and%20ultimately%20did%20not%20work%20out.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20decided%20to%20restart%20my%20career%2C%20this%20time%20in%20tech.%20I%20was%2038.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EFoot%20in%20the%20door%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20I%20had%20learned%20enough%20about%20software%20to%20run%20a%20small%20business%2C%20convincing%20someone%20to%20let%20me%20work%20for%20them%20was%20a%20different%20ball%20game.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGiven%20the%20amount%20of%20competition%20in%20the%20industry%20and%20my%20non-computer%20science%20background%2C%20I%20knew%20I%20had%20to%20work%20hard%20to%20stand%20apart.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20is%20the%20four-step%20plan%20I%20used%20to%20land%20my%20first%20software%20job.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Col%3E%3Cli%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ESpend%20time%20with%20people%20in%20the%20industry%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20ditched%20networking%20on%20LinkedIn.%20I%20would%20try%20to%20meet%20people%20for%20coffee%20and%20put%20myself%20in%20places%20where%20developers%20and%20engineers%20congregated%2C%20such%20as%20conferences.%20The%20idea%20was%20to%20start%20learning%20the%20ways%20of%20the%20industry.%20Instead%20of%20asking%20them%20about%20skills%20I%20needed%20to%20learn%20and%20getting%20cookie-cutter%20answers%2C%20I%20asked%20people%20what%20they%20did%20every%20day.%20It%20gave%20me%20my%20biggest%20advantage%20%E2%80%94%20being%20able%20to%20speak%20to%20engineers%20in%20their%20language.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EIdentify%20employers%20that%20need%20someone%20like%20me%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20focused%20on%20companies%20with%20fewer%20applicants%20and%20high%20turnover%3A%20those%20that%20are%20smaller%2C%20high-pressure%2C%20and%20don't%20pay%20as%20much%20as%20Big%20Tech.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ESkip%20LinkedIn's%20%26quot%3Beasy%20apply%26quot%3B%20function%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOnce%20I%20identified%20that%20small%20web%20development%20agencies%20fit%20the%20bill%2C%20I%20still%20had%20to%20convince%20them%20to%20take%20a%20chance%20on%20me.%20I%20showed%20up%20at%20their%20offices%20and%20asked%20if%20they%20were%20hiring%20developers.%20Talking%20to%20people%20in%20person%20or%20on%20the%20phone%20gave%20me%20a%20chance%20to%20embrace%20how%20%26quot%3Bcrazy%26quot%3B%20it%20was%20that%20I%20was%20an%20ex-lawyer%20switching%20careers%20at%2038%20and%20that%20I%20was%20risking%20a%20lot%20to%20work%20for%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EBuild%20connections%20with%20recruiters%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20realized%20that%20most%20people%20are%20nice%20to%20recruiters%20until%20they%20get%20what%20they%20