ider.com%2F662ed816ec0c696569fe866b%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223024%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ENFL%20fans%20near%20the%20draft%20stage%20at%20Campus%20Martius%20Park%20in%20downtown%20Detroit%20on%20April%2027%2C%202024.%20The%20Renaissance%20Center%20is%20seen%20in%20the%20background%2C%20slightly%20to%20the%20right.%3Cp%3ERyan%20Kang%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Ch2%3EThe%20past%20informs%20the%20present%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20the%201980s%20and%201990s%2C%20downtown%20Detroit%20was%20a%20visible%20reminder%20of%20the%20%26quot%3Burban%20doom%20loop%2C%26quot%3B%20when%20residents%20head%20for%20the%20exits%20and%20office%20towers%20empty%20out%20%E2%80%94%20leading%20to%20diminishing%20tax%20revenues%20that%20threaten%20core%20municipal%20services.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20legendary%20flagship%20location%20of%20Hudson's%20department%20store%2C%20beloved%20by%20generations%20of%20Detroiters%2C%20closed%20in%201983.%20The%201980s%20saw%20scores%20of%20layoffs%20in%20the%20automobile%20industry%20and%20the%20closing%20of%20numerous%20factories%2C%20causing%20economic%20strain%20in%20a%20region%20once%20known%20for%20its%20prosperity%20and%20its%20gateway%20to%20the%20middle%20class.%20Many%20small%20businesses%20either%20closed%20up%20shop%20or%20moved%20to%20the%20region's%20suburbs%2C%20a%20trend%20that%20continued%20into%20the%201990s.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20when%20the%20city%20of%20Detroit%20filed%20for%20Chapter%209%20bankruptcy%20in%20July%202013%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.npr.org%2F2023%2F07%2F22%2F1189093540%2Fdetroit-bankruptcy-comeback-hurdle%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ethe%20largest%20municipal%20bankruptcy%20filing%20in%20US%20history%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20many%20wondered%20whether%20an%20economic%20comeback%20would%20ever%20be%20fully%20realized.%20At%20the%20time%2C%20even%20weekly%20trash%20pickup%20had%20become%20unreliable%20in%20many%20neighborhoods.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENow%2C%20the%20city%20is%20seemingly%20in%20its%20best%20economic%20position%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Ein%20decades.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDetroit%20beat%20out%20Miami%20as%20the%20fastest-appreciating%20housing%20market%20in%20the%20country%20last%20November%2C%20with%20home%20prices%20rising%20by%208.7%25%20year-over-year%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businesswire.com%2Fnews%2Fhome%2F20240109628017%2Fen%2FCoreLogic-US-Home-Price-Growth-Speeds-Up-Again-in-November%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eaccording%20to%20a%20CoreLogic%20report%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%228368%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Hudson's%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F662ed9510dfb1341e9001616%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%225584%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20future%20headquarters%20of%20General%20Motors%20will%20be%20located%20at%20Hudson's%20Detroit.%3Cp%3ESpencer%20Platt%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Ch2%3EPeople%20want%20to%20live%20in%20the%20city%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20allure%20of%20walkable%20neighborhoods%2C%20public%20transportation%2C%20green%20spaces%2C%20and%20businesses%20catering%20to%20local%20needs%20is%20something%20that%20many%20millennials%20and%20Gen%20Zs%20have%20embraced%20with%20open%20arms%20%E2%80%94%20but%20it's%20also%20a%20quality%20attractive%20to%20many%20boomers%20headed%20into%20retirement.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDowntown%20Detroit%20has%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nytimes.com%2F2018%2F03%2F26%2Ftravel%2Farchitecture-detroit-albert-kahn.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ean%20abundance%20of%20towering%2C%20historic%20buildings%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20are%20perfect%20for%20office-to-housing%20conversions%20and%20office%20renovations%20that%20have%20taken%20hold%20in%20downtowns%20across%20the%20country.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDan%20Gilbert%2C%20the%20cofounder%20of%20Rocket%20Mortgage%20(formerly%20Quicken%20Loans)%20and%20a%20Detroit%20native%2C%20has%20poured%20billions%20into%2